!! Introduction

''Works with TW >= v5.4.0''

The ''TW MCP'' plugin adds a [[Model Context Protocol|https://modelcontextprotocol.io/]] (MCP) server to TiddlyWiki. This lets AI assistants like Claude, Gemini, and others read, search, render, and modify your wiki content through a standardised interface.

!! Prerequisites

You need Node.js (v24+), TiddlyWiki (globally installed), and the `TIDDLYWIKI_PLUGIN_PATH` environment variable pointing to the tw-mcp plugin location. See [[MCP Installation]] for detailed setup instructions.

!! Quick Start

!!! 1. Start the MCP server

From your wiki directory run:

```
cd /your/wiki/dir
tiddlywiki . --mcp
```

This starts the MCP server in ''readonly'' mode using stdio transport. The `tiddlywiki/filesystem` plugin is auto-loaded for disk persistence.

; Common options
: `rw` or `readwrite` — enable write operations (readonly is the default)
: `label=<name>` — identify this instance (e.g. `label=claude`)
: `listen` — also start an HTTP server so browser and MCP share the same wiki store

Examples:

This command starts an MCP server with read-write access:

```
cd /your/wiki/dir
tiddlywiki . --mcp rw
```

This command starts an MCP server ''and'' a TiddlyWiki server, which have access to the same wiki-store. So changes written to the store will be directly visible in the browser with the next poll (default 60s).

```
cd /your/wiki/dir
tiddlywiki . --mcp rw listen label=primary port=8080
```

!!! 2. Register with an AI client

See [[MCP Installation]] for `.mcp.json` setup (Claude Code) and [[MCP Gemini Configuration]] for Gemini CLI.

!! Available Tools

The server provides 18 tools for reading, editing, inspecting, and exporting wiki content. See [[MCP Basics]] for the full tool table and [[MCP Instructions]] for detailed usage of each tool.

